GITAM University, Visakhapatnam, is organising a career guidance conference in association with The Hindu School edition in Mangaluru on Monday.The event will be held at Milagres PU College, Hampanakatte, from 10.30 a.m. The aim is to create awareness among pre-university students about professional and general higher education courses, selection of engineering branches and selection of institutes.Experts will talk on choosing the best engineering, pharmacy, or architecture colleges. Lectures will be delivered on science programmes, and research and national level tests.The conference will also cover management education, particularly at the undergraduate level.Details on opportunities for the postgraduate management students or budding managers will be given. Experts will also give brief information about the standards of higher education vis-Ã -vis the functional role of other statutory agencies.There will be a special question and answer session. Entry to the conference is free and spot registration may be made. For details, call M.J. Mathew on 9980771213/ 2417575.